ansplantation rates, particularly promoting collaborative working amongst organisations and raising awareness of donation in the Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic population.</p><p> </p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-09-16T14:53:05.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582025/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582025/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/582025/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-09-12","Kidneys: Transplant Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of kidney transplants in (a) England, (b) Wales, (c) Northern Ireland in each year since 2011; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","46026"
